properties.name: The Old Train Station - The water tower
properties.description: The Old Station - it should have been in the city’s center, but at the end of the ’60, it was moved with a km and half at the west of the city’s center. It remained nothing from the Old Station (except the Water Tower, being intact today) due to the fact that it was demolished, the rails have been taken out, and on the location of the Old Station and rails were built neighborhoods. The new station from Baia Mare was built at the beginning of the years ’70. The Baia Mare Station is a railway junction, situated on the artery 400 of the Romanian Railways. The station is opened for the intern and international traffic, being daily a train from Baia Mare to Budapest.

properties.name: Stephen’s Tower - the image of Baia Mare city
properties.description:
The Citadel Square - Stephen’s Tower - the image of Baia Mare city - built in the 15th century (1446) at the order of Iancu of Hunedoara and finalized during the reign of Matthias Corvinus (1468) - it’s the bell tower of the old church, having the titular saint of “Saint King Stephen” of Baia Mare. The first reference of the church “Saint Stephen” dates from 1347, but the construction is officially opened in 1387. It is built in the Gothic style and the tower has a height of 50 m. The tower was used for monitoring the possible fires and the strategic surveillance of the city.
Visiting hours:
Monday- Friday: 8.00 AM- 4 PM
Saturday, Sunday: 12 AM- 4 PM
The access in the tower is free. There are no fees for photography and filming.
The Bells’ System, the Old Town’s ruins

properties.name: Saint Stephen Gothic church
properties.description:
The first reference of the church “Saint Stephen” dates from 1347 and is the most important edifice from the medieval period of the Baia Mare town. It's related to the birth of the Rivulus Dominarum settlement (1329). The construction of this Gothic church was finished in 1376, but was inaugurated only in 1385.
The church, built in the citadels' square region, dominated the town of Baia Mare, for hundred of years in a row. After some sequence of events mentioned in documents, its condition was depraved, only to become extinct in the middle of the XIXth century (1847). 
The bells' tower was raised after the building of the church and it took the same name, St. Stephen tower, that remained until nowadays. From this tower, You can see a mark on the ground that outlines the former Gothic church of St. Stephen.

properties.name: The ruins of St. Martin church
properties.description: This ruins were discovered during archaeological excavations that took place in the year 2012, by the County Museum of History and Archaeology Maramures, right in front of the  Holy Trinity Roman-Catholic Cathedral, in the south-east corner of the citadels' square. The church was built in the XVth century and has stopped working in the end of the XVIth century, along with the returning of the Jesuits in town.

properties.name: The ruins of St. Catherine Church
properties.description: This ruins were discovered, also, during the archaeological excavations that took place in the year 2012, on the east wing of the citadels' square. This church was probably built in the XVth century and it was demolished in the year 1724.

properties.name: Hotel „King Stephan” - „Minerul” Complex
properties.description: Hotel „King Stephan” - „Minerul” Complex - the secession architectural style is from the beginning of the 19th century. After the grand opening of the hotel, the nearby old inn of the city became the headquarters of the City Hall. When it was opened, it was one of the most modern buildings from Baia Mare. It was named ″Hotel Stefan Voda″ and we can say that it was the first building from Baia Mare that had electricity, water and canalization (sewage), and in the points of sales from the ground floor it was opened the first library of Romanian book. Nowadays, the hotel Minerul (re-opened in 1910, after it was burnt in 1905), having an auditorium and cinema with loges, restaurant and saloon, is being restored on the exterior.

properties.name: The old inn "Black Eagle″
properties.description:
The old inn "Black Eagle″- built before 1790, located in the historical center of Baia Mare (nowadays, Liberty Square). In 1880 was the headquarters of City Hall. From 1950 until 1999, the building was taken by the Baia Mare Court and the Land Registry Office.
Nowadays, the building is included in a project called ″Business Centre III Millennium″ and it has been restored. The objective is known under the name of M1.

properties.name: Marton Lendvay House
properties.description: Marton Lendvay House- the house was built in the 16th century and it’s special by its interior architecture because at the ground floor and first floor the rooms were arched. In this house, in 1807 was born and lived the Hungarian actor Marton Lendvay, one of the pioneer of the Baia Mare theatre of the 19th century, named ″father of modern theatre from Hungary″. Time changed its usefulness, today being the headquarters of various institutions.

properties.name: Iancu of Hunedoara House or Elizabeth House
properties.description: Iancu of Hunedoara House or Elizabeth House - built in 1446, it’s part of the old medieval castle built by Iancu for his wife, Elizabeth. It is the oldest building in the city and you can find it on the east side of the square. Today, the building is used as a place for temporary exhibitions.

properties.name: The Mint
properties.description:
The Baia Mare Mint - a building built between the years 1734 and 1737, it was a very important building for the city due to the purchasing of precious metals, hammering and coins’ exchange, the patent of metals’ refinement.
Today, the building is the headquarters of Maramures county Museum, section History.
Visiting hours:
Monday- closed
Tuesday- Friday 8.30 AM- 3.30 PM
Saturday-Sunday 10 AM- 2 PM

properties.name: The citadel wall
properties.description: A portion of a few meters lenght of stone wall is situated right next to the County Museum of History and Archeology. This wall connected the Mint with some of the most important buildings from the medieval city of Baia Mare, in the times of the Habsburg Empire. The second picture represents "The medieval city of Baia Mare” - reconstitution from the city plans from 1783. Drawing made by Zamfir Somcutean".

properties.name: Schola Rivulina
properties.description: Historic documents speak about “Schola Rivulina” which functioned in Baia Mare in 1547, and which became a college in 1673, mentioned one hundred years later, in 1773, by Johannes Huber, in his “General Geography”.

properties.name: Teleki Mansion (Teleki Magyar Ház)
properties.description: Sandor Teleki, the Count of Sic (1821- 1892), colonel during the Revolution (1848- 1849), lived in Baia Mare in the latest years of his life. In 1870, he bought 2 houses that were on the right side of the Sasar River and transformed them into a mansion. We found out from a description from 1894 that in front of the mansion were eight tall fir trees. In his personal apartment, composed of a working room and bedroom, Teleki used to collect valuable objects. Today, the spacious house reflects the earlier master’s conception. On the carved gate it can be seen the Teleki monogram, the crown with nine arms. Sandor Teleki died in 1892, in Baia Mare. After 1989, the Protestant Church managed to buy the house, and in present is housing the Hungarian House, the center of the Hungarian cultural and social life. In the yard you can see the Teleki’s statue.

properties.name: The Bridge Gate
properties.description: One of the most important entrances in the medieval town of Baia Mare. Nowadays, it's called Podul Viilor.

properties.name: The Butchers’ Tower
properties.description: The Butchers’ Tower - component of the Baia Mare citadel, was built in the 15th century during the reign of Matthias Corvinus. The tower was also called the tower of the “Munitions” because this was the place where in those times the soldiers kept their weapons and gun powder. It was also called of the “butchers” because this brotherhood had the duty to defend the citadel of the eventual foreign attacks. In fact, we have to mention the fact that this brotherhood was the greatest from those existing in those times in the Baia Mare citadel. Nowadays, the tower is used for different cultural activities.

properties.name: The Holy Trinity Roman-Catholic Cathedral
properties.description: The Holy Trinity Roman-Catholic Cathedral - it’s a place of worship built between the years 1717 and 1720, in a Baroque style. The cathedral is an imposing one also through its interior, being decorated with frescos on the altar and ceiling, with stained glasses and certain statues in the pronaos and nave; it holds also an organ constructed between the years 1940 and 1944.

properties.name: The Lutheran church
properties.description: The Lutheran church - the first wooden church built in 1693 with the help of Prince of Ardeal, Mihaly Apafi I. In 1766, it was detroyed by the Jesuits, so the services have been kept for a while in private houses. On the place of the little church with wooden tower, built in 1805, it has been constructed the actual church between years 1911-1912. The benches, the organ built in 1886, the chandelier and the altar accessories from 1901 are the ones kept from the old church. The altar’s painting was painted in 1903 by Bela Ivanyi Grunwald.

properties.name: The Jewish district
properties.description: The Jewish district - includes the synagogue from Baia Mare, built in 1885. In the same period, there have been constructed a new ritual bathroom, a Jewish school and a Jewish nursery school, a house for the rabbi and a hall for the meetings. The first rabbi of Baia Mare (1919) was Mose Aharon Hacohen Krauss (1886-1944). He came from Hungary and was one of the few rabbis from Transylvania, who graduated from University, being considered an excellent preacher. He was murdered during the Holocaust.

properties.name: The synagogue
properties.description: The synagogue from Baia Mare was built in 1885 in the Transylvanian Baroque style, with a surface of 377 square feet. It was included in the list of historical monuments in Maramures County in 2015.

properties.name: The Cathedral of Dormition of the Mother of God
properties.description: The Cathedral of Dormition of the Mother of God - a Greek - catholic parish church between the years 1905-1911, and in 1930 becomes a cathedral. The building is stated as an historical monument, together with the Episcopal Palace of the Greek-Catholic Episcopacy of Maramures county and the old confessional school, situated all together on Vasile Lucaciu street from Baia Mare city.

properties.name: The Protestant Church
properties.description: The Protestant Church - built at the end of 18th century, in a classicist style. The tower of 50 m height, was constructed in 1836 and housed bells molded in 1814, 1815 and 1847. In 1869, the roof and the wooden elements were destroyed in a fire because of a lightning stroke. The re-building brought it at its actual aspect. The copper tower with its ball and red little flag became the second emblem of the city, after the St. Stephen Tower.

properties.name: The monument of the Romanian Heroes
properties.description: The monument of the Romanian Heroes from the Second World War - ″The Monument of the Romanian Soldier″ was uncovered in 1960 on the Youth Plane from Baia Mare, being dedicated to the Romanian soldiers that have died in the II World War. The memorial work has 10.65 m height and 16 m length and was realized by Andrei Ostap from stone and concrete.

properties.name: The miner statue
properties.description: The miner statue - the freestone opera of the artist Gheza Vida was uncovered in 1958 and replaces an almost identical statue, placed here 7 years ago. The statue is in front of the “Remin” National Company of the Precious and non-ferrous Metals (the ex-school of Junior Engineering Officers Miners or the old State School of Mining).

properties.name: The Copper Smelter
properties.description: The Copper Smelter - opened in 1995, it’s the biggest furnace from Romania and the third industrial construction from Europe (height: 351.5 m, basis opening of 20 m, and in the top has a width of 9 m). The chimney was built of concrete durable to noxae, and on the interior is coated with special brick. The tower is no longer in use.

properties.name: Elder people’s council
properties.description: Elder people’s council - opera of the artist Gheza Vida, representing a statuary group, composed of five characters. The first version of the work was executed in wood (in 1972) and today takes part from the collection of the Baia Mare Artistic Center (the Art Museum).

properties.name: City Park "Queen Mary"
properties.description: The main park of Baia Mare is completely inside the forest and is situated next to the Usturoi valley, wich has picnic arrangements. From here you can hike on different touristic trails, beeing right next to the hills. The park has a lovely train for childrens, a running track, a tennis court and a very nice fish pond.

properties.name: The Youth Park
properties.description: Is situated next to the County Museum of Ethnography and Folk Art Baia Mare and the city's football stadium, within a 5 minute walk from the citadel square (old center).

properties.name: The central park
properties.description: It's the newest park of Baia Mare, beeing inaugurated in 2016. Apart from the benches, trees and grass, you can see here an indoor exhibition of different plants.

properties.name: „Mara” park
properties.description: This is one of the most transited park, in particular by the young ones. It has a playground for little childrens, so a lot of families come here, also. It's very close to the city center, so a lot of people are walking through this park.

properties.name: „RFN” park
properties.description: A very small oasis between concrete. Fountains are the main attractions here.

properties.name: „Dacia” park
properties.description: A small park right in the front of the old cinema „Dacia” and next to the river „Săsar”.

properties.name: „Firiza” dam
properties.description:
„Firiza” dam was built on Firiza river and is next to the village with the same name, village embedded in Baia Mare.
The dam located just 10 km from Baia Mare, was built to supply water to the city, electricity generation and flood control. Also known as Straits, built in 1964, is a buttress dam with a height of 51.5 m and a length of 260 m canopy. The lake behind the dam has a length of 3 km and a width of 1 km and it is stocked with trout and carp.

properties.name: „Berdu” lake
properties.description: This is located right in front of the „Firiza” dam.

properties.name: Bodi - Ferneziu lake
properties.description: This artificial lake is surrounded by a beautiful beech forest and a romantic trail.

properties.name: „Igniș” Peak
properties.description: 1307 m high, is one of the peaks seen from Baia Mare, almost from everywhere. It's, also, a place for paragliding. View from Igniș.

properties.name: "The Virgin Rock"
properties.description: Rock formations that provide a beautiful view of the city. View from the Virgin Rock.

properties.name: „Ștur” waterfall
properties.description: A small waterfall along a forest road.

properties.name: "Limpedea" Columns
properties.description: Volcanic rock formation, near Baia Mare, perfect for climbing. Protected area - geological natural reserve.

properties.name: Horse chestnut (aprox. 200 years)
properties.description: Situated next to the police station.

properties.name: "Pleștioare" Glade
properties.description: A glade surrounded by beautiful beech and fir forests.

properties.name: The Hawk`s Rock
properties.description: Rock formation (840 metres high) which offer a spectacular view over the Firiza Lake and the surroundings.

properties.name: "Firiza - Văratec" Medieval Village
properties.description: A small village with medieval houses built from wood and mud, with roofs out of hay.

properties.name: "The Garlic Valley"
properties.description: A small river that springs up from Morgau hills. Here, you can find a lot of places for barbecue, with wooden tables and benches.

properties.name: "The Apple Glade"
properties.description: A small glade with nut trees, surrounded by beech forests, named "The Apple" during the war, used as a refugee.

properties.name: "Borcut" spring
properties.description: A spring of mineral water, known as "borcut".

properties.name: The "Răzvan Givulescu" Fossil Reservation
properties.description: A beech forest with charming paths and informative panels about the reservation, the animals and plants in the area and more.

properties.name: The Artists’ Colony
properties.description:
The Artistic Center of Baia Mare (1896- 2012)
The official document is made by Simon Hollosy in 1896, and from then until now over 4000 artists from different cultural backgrounds in Europe (painters, sculptors, illustrators, ceramists and designers) achieved an artistic heritage of a remarkable richness and diversity. The structure established at the level of the institutions of professional association was built on statuary reasons specific to the category of private and non-governmental organizations, judicial recognized and evolved from the Painters’ Society of Baia Mare (1911, reconfirmed in 1924; dissolved in 1935 and re-activated between 1940 and 1945) to the Artists’ Society of Baia Mare (1937- 1940), the Syndicate of the Artists, Actors and Journalists of Baia Mare (1945- 1949), and finally, starting with year 1950- to the Baia Mare branch office of the Artists’ Union from Romania, to whom it has associated since 1998 the Association “Branch office of the Artists’ Union” Baia Mare, that today has over 100 members and is one of the most dynamic components of the creators’ association of visual art from the whole Romania.

properties.name: UAP Art Gallery
properties.description: Situated in the center of Baia Mare, it's the most important local art gallery.

properties.name: Ephemeral flag Hollosy Simon
properties.description: It was rebuilt in 2016, at the 120th anniversary of the Baia Mare's Painting School.

properties.name: Studio Arena 11
properties.description: A live art gallery, where you can see the artists at work or even work with them, situated inside the municipal stadium.

properties.name: The Art Gallery “Oliver Thurman”
properties.description: A small art gallery situated in the old centre, right next to the Iancu of Hunedoara House.

properties.name: County's Art Museum - Baia Mare Artistic centre
properties.description: http://muzeuldeartabaiamare.wordpress.com/

properties.name: ARTE + Foundation
properties.description: www.arteplus.ro

properties.name: Partner Art Gallery
properties.description: A very little art gallery that's selling painting equipment.

properties.name: The little gallery
properties.description: A very little art gallery that's selling painting equipment.

properties.name: Pocol Castle
properties.description:
In the beautiful neighbourhood Borcutului Valley, named after the mineral water spring that is in the area, arrived here at the end of the 19th century the teacher Alexiu Pokol (or Elek Pokol in some documents). He was from Lozna Mare (village situated in the Salaj county), and son of a parish singer from Letca. He graduated the Normal School from Gherla, as shown in the archives of the actual primary school no. 7 of Borcutului Valley, and being a teacher he opened in 1892 the first primary school from the neighbourhood.
The so-called ″castle″, situated in the northern area of the Borcutului Valley, at 3 km from the road that connect Baia Mare to Satu-Mare, was built in 1903 by Alexiu Pokol.
According to the data received from the Technical Directorate of the County Council, in 1928 the Pocol House, together with the mine from Borcutului Valley, arrived in the property of a mining company, and in 1930 the ″castle″ was sold to a Swiss lord, E. Boissanos, in whose property remained until 1948. After that, it was nationalized and used as a nursery, school and house for the employees of the Prospections and Geological Explorations Corporation (PGEC). The documents of the County Council state that changes were made inside the building compared with the initial construction. After the Revolution, the building was used by the General Direction of Social Assistance and Child Protection Maramures County, being here the institutionalized children from all over the county. Recently, the Pocol House was removed from the property of this institution and integrated in the heritage of the County Council of Maramures county. At the moment, the castle is closed.

properties.name: The Sasar mine
properties.description: The biggest mine field of the Maramures county basin. The city is known for the oldest mint from Romania and biggest museum of mineralogy from Europe. The furnace of Baia Mare has 351.5 m and is the third tallest industrial structure from Europe. Then again, the cultural history of the city was influenced by its long tradition in ceramics and painting.

properties.name: Baia Mare Planetarium
properties.description:
It’s the most modern public planetarium from Romania. A fascinating journey amongst the stars, planets and constellations through the only stellar gate from Transylvania.
Visiting hours
Tuesday- Sunday: 9.00 AM- 4.00 PM
Monday: closed
Entry fees: 8 lei adults, 4 lei children The planetarium shows- astronomical demonstrations in the planetarium’s arch- starting hours: 9.00 AM, 11.00 AM, 1.00 PM and 3.00 PM (last entry- at 2.55 PM, the exception being the organized groups with appointment or groups over 10 persons.

properties.name: The ″Victor Gorduza″ Museum of Mineralogy Baia Mare
properties.description:
The museum displays an exhibition on 900 square feet, where there are exhibited over 1000 mineral specimens, rocks and fossils. There are other 15.000 pieces in the institution’s inventory.
The Museum of Mineralogy Baia Mare is the biggest regional museum from Europe, much of the exhibits being considered unique and heritage values.
The unofficial name, cultural by its excellence and unanimously used is the Museum of mine flowers.

properties.name: The Herja mine
properties.description: Entered the mining circle in the 19th century, as a small mine field, which is closed now. The mine water from here rise great environment issues for the villages from the surroundings.

properties.name: Citadel square
properties.description: http://www.dezvoltareurbana.baiamare.ro/piatacetatii/despre.html

properties.name: History and Archeology Museum
properties.description: http://maramuresmuzeu.ro/

properties.name: County Museum of Ethnography and Folk Art
properties.description: County Museum of Ethnography and Folk Art from Baia Mare is located in no 1 Flower Hill and operates in the current building since 1971. The exhibition pavilion of Ethnography and Folk Art has three distinct parts, in which followings are presented/exhibited: primary and secondary traditional trades, crafts and technical installations, objects belonging to folk art, pottery, furniture, household appliances, elements of folk architecture, costumes and interior textiles from the four ethnographic areas of the county (Chioar, Codru, Lapus, Maramures). Village Museum, inaugurated in 1984 in the picturesque landscape of Flowers Hill (6 hectares), includes monuments of four ethnographic regions of Maramures County clustered around wooden church brought from Chechiş.

properties.name: The Municipal Theater
properties.description: http://teatrulbm.ro/

properties.name: „Liviu Borlan” Art school
properties.description:
„Liviu Borlan” Art school was founded in 1960. During more than 50 years of artistic activity, in this institution they have trained generations of amateur and professional artists for different specializations.
http://www.scoaladeartebm.ro/

properties.name: The village museum
properties.description: This outdoor museum is part of the County museum of ethnography and folk art and contains many types of traditional buildings from Maramureș county.

properties.description: http://www.bibliotecamm.ro/
